Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, suggesting impaired glucose metabolism or prediabetes, despite normal fasting glucose. Hemoglobin and hematocrit are slightly elevated, while erythrocyte count is just below normal, possibly indicating hemoconcentration or early erythrocytosis. Platelet distribution width is markedly high, which may reflect platelet anisocytosis but with normal platelet count. Lipid profile and other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation is recommended.
